ANTHRAX - RUSSIA (02): VOLGOGRAD) HUMAN, LIVESTOCK, SUSPECTED
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 11 Aug 2014
Source: RIA Federal Press [in Russian, trans., edited]
http://fedpress.ru/news/econom/runok/1407738458-na-volgogradskii-rynok-proniklo-myaso-s-sibirskoi-yazvoi-provoditsya-proverka


Meat presumably infected with "anthrax", has been sold in the "East" market of Krasnooktyabrskiy region of Volgograd. According to the press service of the governor of the region, the regional law enforcement agencies, health monitoring services, and the veterinary department are investigating. Suspicion of the dangerous infectious disease occurred after the owner of a private farm in Molokanovsky village, Ilmensky Oktyabrsky district, was hospitalized with a preliminary diagnosis of "anthrax." It seems that the man in violation of the rules concerning the use of slaughterhouses, butchered an animal at home for subsequent sale in the "East", market without providing the proper documents to the market dealers. The meat was seized and sent for examination, and law enforcement agencies are trying to find who might have bought this contaminated meat, and how this all came about.

The Ministry of Health has reported that the affected farmer is not in a critical condition. All that is needed to treat anthrax is available to Volgograd physicians, and cutaneous anthrax is considered to be completely curable. The last time that human anthrax was reported in the Volgograd region was in 2010 in a settlement in Surovikinskogo district.

