[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Russia can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2679131,40932. To find Volgograd in southern Russia, go to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volgograd. To find Krasnooktyabrskiy, go to http://www.gomapper.com/travel/where-is/krasnooktyabrskiy-volgograd-located.html.

The Russian oblasts are a long way from Moscow and therefore official reporting is problematic, quite apart from their predilection for reporting only outbreaks that involve human cases. For example, one outbreak in Volgograd (Vodno-Buerachnay, Kamyshinski district) only diagnosed after the sick cow's owner and the slaughterman were hospitalised; the carcass had by then been converted to sausages. There was a single bovine case reported in Volgograd in 2010. Logically there will have been significantly more livestock outbreaks, with and without human cases, in the other years, and since. And in this instance we must await laboratory confirmation. Our thanks to Sabine for this report. - Mod.MHJ]
